\begin_layout Paragraph
get ID [ID ...]
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Get the XML definition of one or more tasks.
 This command takes one or more arguments which are the task IDs and outputs
 the different definitions.
 If more than one task is specified, the definitions are enclosed in an
 XML document
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
prepare ID [ID ...]
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Prepare one or more tasks.
 This command takes a list of task IDs as argument and prepare them by downloadi
ng and processing automatically the different files (topics, qrels)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
evaluate ID <run path>
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Evaluate a run for a given task ID.
